
  Name:  pclose
  
  #include <stdio.h>
  int pclose(FILE *stream);
  
  The pclose() function waits for the associated process to 
  terminate and returns the exit status of the command as returned
  by wait4. The pclose() function returns -1 if wait4(2) returns an 
  error, or some other error is detected.
  
  Related Functions:  fclose, fflush, fopen, stdio, system

